\begin{proof}
  \uses{lem:internal_hom_eval, lem:internal_hom_isSheaf, lem:tensorobj_unit_iso}
  At the presheaf level the dual of the unit \(\mathbf{1} = \mathcal{O}_Y\) is the internal
  hom \(\mathcal{H}om(\mathbf{1}, \mathbf{1})\), whose value on an open \(U\) is the module
  of \(\mathcal{O}(U)\)-linear endomorphisms of \(\mathbf{1}|_U\). Each such endomorphism is
  determined by its value at the global section \(1\) and equals multiplication by that
  value; hence evaluation at \(1\) --- the internal-hom evaluation
  \cref{lem:internal_hom_eval} of the unit, composed with the left unitor
  \(\mathbf{1} \otimes \mathbf{1} \cong \mathbf{1}\) of \cref{lem:tensorobj_unit_iso} --- is
  an isomorphism \(\mathcal{H}om(\mathbf{1}, \mathbf{1}) \cong \mathbf{1}\) of presheaves of
  modules. Sheafifying through the sheaf-level dual of \cref{lem:internal_hom_isSheaf}
  yields \(\mathtt{dual}\,\mathcal{O}_Y \cong \mathcal{O}_Y\).
\end{proof}

